Trump Trades Policy Ideas, Jokes With Manufacturing Leaders at Informal Forum After executives meet with senior administration officials, president recounts hole in one with GE’s Immelt By Google+ Updated Feb. 23, 2017 2:47 p.m. ET 
President Donald Trump convened the leaders of some of the country’s biggest manufacturers at the White House on Thursday to share proposals for overhauling corporate taxes and regulations, and reviving the nation’s manufacturing sector. 
The Trump administration gathered executives from major manufacturers including General Electric Co., Dow Chemical Co., and Lockheed Martin Corp., to trade policy proposals with senior administration officials in a closed-door session at the White House followed by a formal audience with...
